articles.title: Netanyahu And Modi To Meet “Very Soon”: What The Telephonic Call Between Two PMs Signals
articles.description: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu and Indian PM Narendra Modi held a warm strategic phone call, agreeing to meet soon. The leaders discussed West Asia developments, reiterated support for the Gaza Peace Plan, condemned terrorism and emphasised strengthening India-Israel ties across defence, technology and intelligence.
articles.content:
Tel Aviv: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi have agreed to meet “very soon”, following a cordial and friendly phone conversation, the Israeli PM’s office announced on Wednesday (December 10).

articles.title: Kotak Securities sees 13% rise in Nifty by next December
articles.description: Kotak Securities is optimistic about the stock markets, setting a Nifty target of 29,120 by December 2026, driven by strong earnings growth expectations. The brokerage anticipates over 17% earnings growth for 2027, with improved macro conditions and policy decisions expected to fuel gains. They favor BFSI, technology, healthcare, and hospitality sectors, while also noting positive outlooks for gold and silver.
